eaching as far as Nueva Ecija (North Luzon), Tarlac, Bulacan and Pampanga.\n\nAfter the management takeover, DWDU was later on assigned to Comclark's affiliate, Reliance Broadcasting Unlimited.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.untvweb.com/}}\n*[http://www.bmpicorp.com Breakthrough and Milestones Productions International]\n\n{{Metro Manila TV}}\n{{Television in the Philippines}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Information Broadcast Unlimited}}\n[[Category:Philippine television networks]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Metro Manila]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 2001]]\n[[Category:Digital television stations in the Philippines]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toDivision(link changed toDivision (business)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Information_Broadcast_Unlimited"}
